goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?
goals.visualization: Violin plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A violin plot can show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different categories.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield across different sites?
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the frequency distribution of yield for each site, allowing for comparison of the yield distribution across different locations.

goals.question: How does the yield vary between the two years of the study?
goals.visualization: Box plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution for each year, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data between the two years.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and site?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield by site
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and site, allowing for identification of any patterns or trends in the data.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='yield', ax=ax)
    avg_yield = data['yield'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Yield: {avg_yield:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.violinplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='site', multiple='stack', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across different sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Site', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='yield', by='year', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('How does the yield vary between the two years of the study?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Year', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['site'], data['yield'], c=data['year'], cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Site')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between yield and site?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Year")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
